jmortgage.payment
Enum Interval

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<Interval>
      jmortgage.payment.Interval
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<Interval>
public enum Interval
extends Enum<Interval>

Enum that represents the amount of time between payments. This enum is used when building an implementation of PmtCalculator to calcluate the interval payment for a mortgage term. It is used when building an implementation of PmtKey to determine how far to increment subsequent payment keys.

Since:
1.0
Author:
David Armstrong
